Vision der bellezza della città zu. Der Band dokumentiert eine interdisziplinäre Tagung vom 20.-23. September 2001 in der Villa Vigoni am Comer See.  aMedieval Italian urban legislation is well documented. It represents a rich and hitherto inadequately exploited source for studies in the history of art and the history of law. The documents that have come down to us not only provide information on the layout and design of squares, monuments, churches, and fortifications, but also indicate the aesthetic concerns of the authorities involved and their visions of the bellezza della città. The volume is a record of the proceedings of an interdisciplinary symposium that took place at the Villa Vigoni on Lake Como, 20-23 September 2001.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aCities and towns, MedievalzItalyvCongresses. 0aCity planningzItalyxHistoryyTo 1500vCongresses. 0aTown laws, MedievalzItalyxHistoryyTo 1500vCongresses. 4aGeschichte 900-1600. 4aItalien. 4aLoveno ‹Menaggio, 2001›. 4aStadtgestaltung. 4aStadtrecht. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aAscheri, Mario, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaumgärtner, Ingrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDilcher, Gerhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGardner, Julian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuidoni, Enrico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeller, Hagen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKosegarten, Antje Middeldorf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPiergiovanni, Vito, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoeck, Bernd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.